[MATH_TASK] Problem:
Find the quotient when $7x^3 + 3x^2 - 5x - 8$ is divided by $x + 2.$

Solution:
We use long division.

\[
\begin{array}{c|ccccc}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{7x^2} & -5x & -8 \\
\cline{2-6}
x+2 & 7x^3 & +3x^2 & -5x & -8 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{7x^3} & +14x^2 & \\
\cline{2-4}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & -14x^2 & -5x \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & -14x^2 & -28x \\
\cline{3-5}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & 33x - 8 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & 33x - 66 \\
\cline{4-6}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & & 33 \\
\end{array}
\]The quotient is $\boxed{7x^2 - 5x - 8}.$

