\end{align*}

children.text:
The greatest common factor of $32x^3$ and $20x$ is $4x$. We factor $4x$ out of each term to get \begin{align*}
32x^3-4x^2+20x &= 4x\cdot8x^2-4x^2+20x\\
&= \boxed{4x(8x-1)(5x+2)}.
\end{align*}

