\sqrt[6]{-64} &= \sqrt[6]{64}e^{\frac{8\pi i}{6}} = 2e^{\frac{8\pi i}{6}} \\
-\sqrt[6]{64} &= -\sqrt[6]{64}e^{\frac{10\pi i}{6}} = -2e^{\frac{10\pi i}{6}} \\
\sqrt[6]{-64} &= \sqrt[6]{64}e^{\frac{12\pi i}{6}} = 2e^{\frac{12\pi i}{6}} \\
-\sqrt[6]{64} &= -\sqrt[6]{64}e^{\frac{14\pi i}{6}} = -2e^{\frac{14\pi i}{6}}
\end{align*}

Thus, the 6th roots of $-64$ are $2e^{\frac{2\pi i}{6}}, -2e^{\frac{4\pi i}{6}}, 2e^{\frac{8\pi i}{6}}, -2e^{\frac{10\pi i}{6}}, 2e^{\frac{12\pi i}{6}}, -2e^{\frac{14\pi i}{6}}$.  These are 6th roots of unity, so they are of the form $a+bi$ where $a$ and $b$ are real.  We can write these solutions in the form $a+bi$ as follows:

