(x+3)(2x-4)(x-6) &= (x+3)(2x^2-8x+12x-24)\\
&= (x+3)(2x^2+4x-24).
\end{align*}We use the distributive property again to multiply $(x+3)(2x^2+4x-24)$: \begin{align*}
(x+3)(2x^2+4x-24) &= x(2x^2+4x-24)+3(2x^2+4x-24)\\
&= \boxed{2x^3+4x^2-24x+6x^2+12x-72}.
\end{align*}

