label("$a + bi$", B, NE);
label("$b$", C, W);
[/asy]

Since $2 - 7i$ is pure imaginary, $2 - 7i = 0$, so $2 = -7i$.  Since $b = \frac{a}{b}$, $a = -14i$.  Therefore, $\frac{a}{b} = \boxed{-\frac{14}{1}}.$

