children.text:
[asy]
unitsize(0.5 cm);

pair P, Q;

P = (2,1);
Q = (1,-2);

draw(P--Q);
draw(P--(-2,0)--Q,dashed);

dot("$P$", P, NW);
dot("$Q$", Q, SW);
[/asy]

We can solve for $PQ$ by using the formula for the distance between a point and a line.  Let $P = (a,a,a).$  Then
\[PQ = \frac{Q - P}{\| Q - P \|}.\]We can express $Q$ in terms of $P$ as follows:
\[Q = \left( \frac{2 - a}{2}, a, \frac{3 - a}{2} \right).\]Then
\[PQ = \frac{Q - P}{\| Q - P \|} = \frac{\left( \frac{2 - a}{2} \right) - a}{\sqrt{\left( \frac{2 - a}{2} \right)^2 + a^2 + \left( \frac{3 - a}{2} \right)^2}} = \frac{\frac{a + 4 - 2a}{2}}{\sqrt{\frac{a^2 + 4a + 4}{4} + \frac{9 - 6a + a^2}{4}}} = \frac{1}{2} \cdot \frac{1}{1 + \frac{a}{2}}.\]We want to minimize $PQ,$ so we want to maximize $\frac{1}{1 + \frac{a}{2}}.$  We can achieve this by taking $a = 2,$ so $PQ = \boxed{1}.$

