[MATH_TASK] Problem:
Three congruent isosceles triangles $DAO,$ $AOB,$ and $OBC$ have $AD=AO=OB=BC=10$ and $AB=DO=OC=12.$ These triangles are arranged to form trapezoid $ABCD,$ as shown. Point $P$ is on side $AB$ so that $OP$ is perpendicular to $AB.$ [asy]
pair A, B, C, D, O, P;
A= (6, 8);
B=(18, 8);
C=(24, 0);
D=(0,0);
O=(12,0);
P=(12,8);
draw(A--B--C--D--A);
draw(A--O--B);
draw(O--P, dashed);
label("A", A, NW);
label("B", B, NE);
label("C", C, SE);
label("D", D, SW);
label("O", O, S);
label("P", P, N);
label("12", (D+O)/2, S);
label("12", (O+C)/2, S);
label("10", (A+D)/2, NW);
label("10", (B+C)/2, NE);
[/asy] What is the length of $OP?$

Solution:
Since $\triangle AOB$ is isosceles, $AB = AO = 12.$  In $\triangle ADO,$ by the Pythagorean Theorem,
\[AD = \sqrt{AO^2 - OD^2} = \sqrt{12^2 - 6^2} = 8 \sqrt{3}.\]In $\triangle DOB,$
\[DB = \sqrt{DO^2 - OB^2} = \sqrt{8^2 - 6^2} = 6 \sqrt{3}.\]Then $OP = AB - DB = 12 - 6 \sqrt{3} = \boxed{12 - 6 \sqrt{3}}.$

