Also, $OP$ is perpendicular to $AB,$ so $OP \perp AB.$ Since $P$ is on $AB,$ we have $OP = PB.$

By the Pythagorean Theorem, we have \begin{align*}
AB^2 &= AP^2 + PB^2 \\
&= OP^2 + PB^2 \\
&= OP^2 + (OP - 8)^2 \\
